en_1048531_0	The Cabinet Sub-Committee on Cost of Living has made temporary changes to the taxes on a number of essential items.
en_1048531_1	They have also announced the distribution of a bag of essential items worth Rs.5000 will be to those affected by the drought for the next two months.
en_1048531_2	Taxes have been removed on 47 essential items including rice, sugar, potatoes, big onions and replaced them with a special commodities tax.
en_1048531_3	The Special Commodity Levy for one kilogram of imported rice has been reduced from five rupees to 25 cents.
en_1048531_4	The newly announced commodity levy will end on December 31.
en_1048531_5	The Special Commodity Levy for imported wet fish has been reduced from Rs.50 a kilogram to Rs,10 a kilo with effect from today,  and will be in effect for the next three months.
en_1048531_6	All duties imposed on corn used in chicken food products have been removed and replaced with a ten rupee Special Commodity Levy from today onwards and will be in effect for the next six months.
en_1048531_7	Until now, the tax on corn included; Import Tax – 15% VAT – 15% Port and Airport Tax – 7.5% Nation Building Tax – 2% CESS tax – 35% All these taxes on corn tallied up to around Rs.
en_1048531_8	60/- to Rs.
en_1048531_9	70/- in taxes.
en_1048531_10	Ten rupees have been reduced from the CESS tax of a kilogram of wheat flour, thereby reducing the tax from Rs.
en_1048531_11	25 to Rs.15.
en_1048531_12	The above changes will come into effect in the coming days.
en_1048531_13	The Finance Ministry further notes that the required tax amendments would be made for local food products when entering the market to protect the farmer.
en_1048531_14	These decisions have been taken under the directive of President Maithripala Sirisena.
en_1048531_15	They were announced by Minister of Finance and Mass Media, Mangala Samaraweera.
